questiontext.text:
Below is an incomplete Free Body Diagram.

Use the information given in the image above and the knowledge that the beam weighs 10N/cm to complete the Free Body Diagram.

You should indicate both the values of the loads and the distances from the start position of the beam.

Use the Free Body Diagram to determine the magnitude of Reaction Forces R1 and R2.

(For the purposes of this question, you may take g=10 ms-2.)

generalfeedback.text:
When drawing Free Body Diagrams, Uniformly Distributed Loads (UDLs) are represented as a point load at the midpoint of the UDL.

Do not forget to convert mass in kilograms to mass in Newtons before completing the question.
